Compsci 61* instead 16!

Options is how you switch sections, yes.

If you are enrolled and the lab you are trying to switch to has open space for you, then you would not be moved into the waitlist. If there wasn't open space, you would be moved into the waitlist in the first position for the class (i.e. you would have priority over the students already on the waitlist there, since you were enrolled).

Please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu if you have EE/EECS enrollment questions as I am not answering questions here. 

If you use the options function, I would guess you would have the issue posted above so I recommend waiting until it's resolved.

history.content:
Update 1/16

Central campus has blocked enrollment in EE 16a/b & 61 b/c  until the swap issue is resolved (see @5947). There is nothing the department can do until this is resolved by Cal Central. 

Enrollment has not been blocked in the other EE classes. If you have issues with the other EE classes (C128, 49, 130, and any other EE 3-component class) email sishelp@berkeley.edu and include your SID and which sections you prefer to enroll in. They may be able to process this for you, if there is an open seat.

----

This message is from the Office of the Registrar. They are working on the problem, but please contact sishelp@berkeley.edu if you have this issue so they can track everything. Nor Cindy or myself can fix this, unfortunately.
"There is currently an issue where students are dropped from their discussion or lab, if they perform a discussion or lab change in a 3 component class set up. The issue occurs if the class is set up in the following format:
Lecture - enrollment component
Discussion and lab - non enrollment component
If the class is set up with lecture, discussion, and lab, the issue will occur if the student attempts to swap out either the discussion or the lab (only one).
Common classes which students experience the issue:
  • ELENG 16A, 16B, C128, 49, 130
  • COMPSCI 61 B and C
  • ENGIN 7A
Example:
Enrolled in Lecture 001
Enrolled in Discussion 101
Enrolled in Lab 201
If the student attempts to swap discussion 101 to 102 (lecture and lab is not swapped), the error occurs and student is dropped from the discussion completely (currently enrolled discussion is dropped and newly requested discussion is not added). Student will then only be enrolled in a lecture and lab (incorrectly).
If the student swaps both discussion and lab, the error will not occur.
The issue is being reviewed for a permanent solution."
